00:34:18,217 --> 00:34:20,276
Where are we, Coffey?

448
00:34:20,386 --> 00:34:24,482
This is the forward
berthing compartment. This way.

449
00:34:28,460 --> 00:34:30,951
<i>[Hull Groaning]</i>

450
00:34:39,438 --> 00:34:42,965
<i>[Bud]
You guys okay? Cat? Jammer?</i>

451
00:34:43,075 --> 00:34:46,476
<i>- Right behind you, Bud.
- Check your gauges.</i>

452
00:34:47,579 --> 00:34:51,015
<i>- How's your O-2?
- I'm okay.</i>

453
00:34:51,116 --> 00:34:55,815
<i>- Gauges are good.
- Okay, 16 minutes to go.</i>

454
00:35:06,365 --> 00:35:09,425
<i>[Hippy]
Jammer, your C-O-2 is up.</i>

455
00:35:09,535 --> 00:35:12,265
<i>- Breathe slower, Buddy.
- [Jammer] I'm okay.</i>

456
00:35:18,777 --> 00:35:22,873
[Coffey]
Come on. Let's keep up.

457
00:35:22,981 --> 00:35:26,109
All right. Up this way
to the control center.

458
00:35:49,174 --> 00:35:52,837
[Straining]

459
00:35:52,945 --> 00:35:57,746
- It's jammed. Give me a hand.
- Get up here with that pry bar.

460
00:35:58,884 --> 00:36:01,011
It's moving!
Pull!

461
00:36:09,428 --> 00:36:11,328
Jesus!

462
00:36:11,430 --> 00:36:16,231
All right. We knew we were
gonna see this. Just move on.

463
00:36:19,671 --> 00:36:22,606
Come on, Jammer.
Let's go.

464
00:36:57,409 --> 00:36:59,877
<i>[Bud]
Okay, let's stay cool.</i>

465
00:36:59,978 --> 00:37:02,105
Everybody stay cool.

466
00:37:02,214 --> 00:37:07,151
We can't help these guys,
but we might find somebody further in.

467
00:37:13,559 --> 00:37:15,459
Stay here.

468
00:37:29,575 --> 00:37:31,600
[Breathes Heavily]

469
00:37:31,710 --> 00:37:35,043
- Hey, Jammer. You okay?
- Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

470
00:37:35,147 --> 00:37:37,741
How you guys doin'?

471
00:37:37,850 --> 00:37:41,479
- I'm dealin'.
- Triple time sounded like
a lot of money, Bud. It ain't.

472
00:37:41,587 --> 00:37:43,521
We're here.
Let's get 'er done.

473
00:37:43,622 --> 00:37:47,456
Brigman, take your men
and continue aft.

474
00:37:47,559 --> 00:37:50,687
Split up into two teams.

475
00:37:50,796 --> 00:37:53,856
Come on. Let's get moving.
We head back in 14 minutes.

476
00:37:53,966 --> 00:37:56,457
Let's go.

477
00:38:04,076 --> 00:38:06,044
[Bud]
You okay, Jammer?

478
00:38:06,144 --> 00:38:08,044
<i>Yeah, fine.</i>

479
00:38:13,285 --> 00:38:16,777
<i>- What's this?
- It should be the missile
launch control center.</i>

480
00:38:16,889 --> 00:38:19,949
<i>- Don't touch anything.
- No, no, no, no, no.</i>

481
00:38:20,058 --> 00:38:22,322
[Chuckles]
This way.

482
00:38:22,427 --> 00:38:24,395
Right behind you.

483
00:38:45,317 --> 00:38:47,785
- You still with me, Jammer?
- Where are we?

484
00:38:47,886 --> 00:38:51,413
Missile compartment.
Those are the launch tubes.

485
00:38:59,031 --> 00:39:03,764
Shit! Shit, shit, shit!
[Breathing Heavily]

486
00:39:03,869 --> 00:39:07,066
Hey, Jammer.

487
00:39:07,172 --> 00:39:10,733
Hey! Hey! Hey!
Hey! Hey! Hey! You okay?

488
00:39:10,842 --> 00:39:12,901
Deep and slow,
big guy.

489
00:39:13,011 --> 00:39:15,343
Deep and slow.
Just breathe easy.

490
00:39:15,447 --> 00:39:17,711
Everybody's dead!
They're all dead.

491
00:39:17,816 --> 00:39:20,580
- I'm taking you back out. Let's go.
- No!

492
00:39:20,686 --> 00:39:22,916
I'm okay. I'm okay.

493
00:39:27,326 --> 00:39:31,456
- I just can't go any further in.
- Okay, Jammer. No problem.
You stay right here.

494
00:39:31,563 --> 00:39:34,691
I've got to check out
this compartment, all right?

495
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:38,861
We'll stay in voice contact.
You hold on the end of this rope here.

496
00:39:38,971 --> 00:39:43,169
- You have any problem whatsoever,
you tug twice.
- I got it.

497
00:39:43,275 --> 00:39:47,575
Pull it hard. Five more minutes.
Just relax. You'll be okay.

498
00:39:47,679 --> 00:39:50,273
- Okay.
- Be right back.

499
00:39:54,987 --> 00:39:57,888
[Breathing Heavily]

500
00:40:07,566 --> 00:40:10,467
[Heavy Breathing Continues]

501
00:40:34,609 --> 00:40:37,669
You still readin' me
okay, big guy?

502
00:40:37,779 --> 00:40:39,940
<i>[Jammer]
Read you fine, Bud.</i>

503
00:40:45,187 --> 00:40:48,122
Okay, just a few
more minutes.

504
00:40:48,223 --> 00:40:52,091
There's a couple compartments
up ahead that might have air.

505
00:40:52,194 --> 00:40:55,186
<i>- Okay, no problem.
- We got to be sure, right?</i>

506
00:40:55,297 --> 00:40:59,131
<i>Hang on, Jammer. You just hold
on to that...[Transmission Fades]</i>

507
00:41:04,906 --> 00:41:08,467
Shit!
Bud?

508
00:41:08,577 --> 00:41:12,206
Bud, can you hear me?
Bud? Bud?

509
00:41:14,716 --> 00:41:16,616
Goddamn it!

510
00:41:20,589 --> 00:41:22,682
[Hyperventilating]

511
00:41:29,764 --> 00:41:32,028
Oh, Jesus!

512
00:41:44,579 --> 00:41:47,480
[Breathing Slows]

513
00:42:00,161 --> 00:42:02,561
Bud, is that you?

514
00:42:21,683 --> 00:42:24,948
[Loud Bang]

515
00:42:25,053 --> 00:42:28,614
Hang on, Jammer.

516
00:42:28,723 --> 00:42:34,184
- [Hyperventilating]
- Lew, Cat, hurry up! On the double!

517
00:42:34,296 --> 00:42:36,526
<i>[Lew]
I'm on my way.</i>

518
00:42:42,337 --> 00:42:47,206
- Jammer!
- [Gurgling]

519
00:42:47,309 --> 00:42:50,244
<i>- What's the problem?
- He's convulsing!</i>

520
00:42:51,346 --> 00:42:54,747
It's his mixture.
Too much oxygen.

521
00:42:54,849 --> 00:42:59,843
Got to get the O-2 cut down!
Turn him over!

522
00:42:59,955 --> 00:43:03,049
Crank it down, man!
You're losin' him!

523
00:43:05,026 --> 00:43:09,986
All right. We got to get him
out of here. Let's go. Let's move it.

524
00:43:10,098 --> 00:43:13,329
Easy, big fella.
That's it.

525
00:43:13,435 --> 00:43:16,996
One Night, do you see the divers?
Are they out yet?

526
00:43:17,105 --> 00:43:21,132
Negative, Lindsey.
Haven't seen hide nor hair.

527
00:43:21,242 --> 00:43:25,042
Let's give them two minutes more max,
and then I'll sound a diver recall...

528
00:43:45,934 --> 00:43:47,959
[Bud Over Radio]
Lindsey, do you copy?

529
00:43:48,069 --> 00:43:52,165
Meet me at Flatbed. This is a diver
emergency. Linds, do you copy?

530
00:43:52,273 --> 00:43:55,401
Uh, yeah, copy you, Bud.
L-I'm on my way.

531
00:44:00,882 --> 00:44:05,819
Look, I'm just a medic,
which is mostly about patchin' holes.

532
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:11,017
This type of thing, it's...
There's not much I can do.

533
00:44:11,126 --> 00:44:14,027
A coma could last
hours or days.

534
00:44:20,602 --> 00:44:23,469
So you didn't get
anything on the cameras.

535
00:44:23,571 --> 00:44:25,903
No. I didn't get
a picture of it.

536
00:44:26,007 --> 00:44:28,134
- What about the video?
- No.

537
00:44:28,243 --> 00:44:33,112
We lost power right then. Look, I just
don't want to talk about this, okay?

538
00:44:33,214 --> 00:44:35,876
Fine. Be that way.

539
00:44:35,984 --> 00:44:38,418
Look, I don't know
what I saw, Bud, okay?

540
00:44:38,520 --> 00:44:42,650
Coffey wants to call it
a Russian submersible, fine,
it's a Russian submersible.

541
00:44:42,757 --> 00:44:47,285
- No problem.
- Yeah, but you think
it was somethin' else.

542
00:44:47,395 --> 00:44:51,058
What?
One of ours?

543
00:44:54,469 --> 00:44:57,404
- No.
- Well, whose then?

544
00:44:59,340 --> 00:45:02,503
Come on, Lindsey,
talk to me.

545
00:45:02,610 --> 00:45:06,444
Look, Jammer saw something
down there, something that
scared the hell out of him.

546
00:45:06,548 --> 00:45:10,177
His mixture got screwed up.
Jammer panicked.

547
00:45:10,285 --> 00:45:12,845
He pranged his regulator,
and his mixture got screwed up.

548
00:45:12,954 --> 00:45:15,388
But what did he see
that made him panic?

549
00:45:17,425 --> 00:45:19,393
Well, what do you
think he saw?

550
00:45:21,362 --> 00:45:23,660
I don't know.

551
00:45:23,765 --> 00:45:27,826
- Did any of you see it?
- No, sir. The Brigman woman saw it.

552
00:45:27,936 --> 00:45:29,904
It could have been
a Russian bogey.

553
00:45:30,004 --> 00:45:34,771
Oh, Cinclantfleet's
gonna go ape shit.

554
00:45:34,876 --> 00:45:38,972
Two Russian attack subs,
a Tango and a Victor,
were tracked within 50 miles of here.

555
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:42,481
<i>Now they don't know
where the hell they are. Okay.</i>

556
00:45:42,584 --> 00:45:45,576
[Sighs]
I haven't got any choice.

557
00:45:45,687 --> 00:45:48,053
I'm confirming you
to go to phase two.

558
00:45:48,156 --> 00:45:50,488
<i>You'll recover
one warhead, arm it...</i>

559
00:45:50,592 --> 00:45:51,559
<i>and wait for
further instructions.</i>

560
00:45:54,244 --> 00:45:57,475
- We got a problem with that?
- Negative, sir.

561
00:45:59,016 --> 00:46:02,213
- [Whistles] Better come on.
- Turn it up, folks.

562
00:46:02,319 --> 00:46:05,447
<i>Sources have not confirmed any reports
that the Montana encountered...</i>

563
00:46:05,556 --> 00:46:08,616
a Soviet fast-attack sub
prior to its sinking,

564
00:46:08,725 --> 00:46:11,751
and the Kremlin continues
to deny any involvement.

565
00:46:11,862 --> 00:46:13,955
Oh, that's us.
That's us, man.

566
00:46:14,064 --> 00:46:17,659
Benthic Petroleum are apparently
participating in the recovery operation,

567
00:46:17,768 --> 00:46:20,202
but we have little information
about their involvement.

568
00:46:20,304 --> 00:46:22,772
Bullshit.
We want names.

569
00:46:22,873 --> 00:46:25,569
<i>- That's the Explorer. We're famous.
- Shh, quiet.</i>

570
00:46:25,676 --> 00:46:29,407
There is a tremendous
amount of activity.

571
00:46:29,513 --> 00:46:31,743
With Cuba only 80 miles away,

572
00:46:31,848 --> 00:46:34,078
the massive buildup
of American forces...

573
00:46:34,184 --> 00:46:37,449
has drawn official protest
from Havana and Moscow.

574
00:46:37,554 --> 00:46:42,116
<i>Russian and Cuban trawlers,
undoubtedly surveillance vessels,</i>

575
00:46:42,226 --> 00:46:44,456
<i>have been circling
the area,</i>

576
00:46:44,561 --> 00:46:48,258
<i>- and Soviet aircraft have
repeatedly been warned away.
- This sucks.</i>

577
00:46:48,365 --> 00:46:50,765
Hippy, what's the matter
with you?

578
00:46:50,867 --> 00:46:52,767
What's the matter with me?
Nothing.

579
00:46:52,869 --> 00:46:55,770
We're just in the middle
of some big-time international incident,

580
00:46:55,872 --> 00:46:57,840
like the Cuban missile crisis
or something.

581
00:46:57,941 --> 00:47:00,068
Figured that out for yourself,
did you, Hip?

582
00:47:00,177 --> 00:47:02,077
We got Russian subs
creepin' around.

583
00:47:02,179 --> 00:47:06,081
Anything goes wrong, they could say
whatever they want happened.

584
00:47:06,183 --> 00:47:08,674
Relax, will you?
You're makin' the women nervous.

585
00:47:08,785 --> 00:47:13,415
- Cute, Virgil.
- You know, those SEALs
ain't telling us diddly.

586
00:47:13,523 --> 00:47:15,957
- Somethin' is going on!
- Come on, come on.

587
00:47:16,059 --> 00:47:18,493
Hippy, you think everything's
a conspiracy.

588
00:47:18,595 --> 00:47:20,495
Everything is.

589
00:47:20,597 --> 00:47:23,259
Hurry up!
Coffey's splitting with Flatbed.

590
00:47:23,367 --> 00:47:26,393
- I showed him how to work the controls,
and they're outta here.
- Damn it.

591
00:47:26,503 --> 00:47:29,597
- Didn't you tell him
we need it right now?
- He didn't pay attention.

592
00:47:29,706 --> 00:47:31,936
<i>- Where the hell is he taking it?
- I have no idea!</i>

593
00:47:32,042 --> 00:47:35,603
Shit! Coffey! Come back!

594
00:47:35,712 --> 00:47:39,273
We need the big arm
to unhook the umbilical.

595
00:47:39,383 --> 00:47:42,648
There's a goddamn
hurricane comin'!

596
00:47:42,753 --> 00:47:45,119
<i>- He switched off.
- It's unbelievable.</i>

597
00:47:45,222 --> 00:47:48,089
Go back down.

598
00:47:48,191 --> 00:47:51,786
Tell those men to get below
and stay there.

599
00:48:02,506 --> 00:48:05,236
We need to get unhooked
and get out of here now.

600
00:48:05,342 --> 00:48:07,242
All right, do it then.

601
00:48:07,344 --> 00:48:10,074
No problem, except your boys
went sightseeing with Flatbed.

602
00:48:10,180 --> 00:48:12,808
My people need Flatbed
to get unhooked at their end.

603
00:48:12,916 --> 00:48:15,043
- Back in two hours.
- Two hours?

604
00:48:15,152 --> 00:48:18,849
We're gonna get the shit kicked
out of us by our pal Fred in two hours.

605
00:48:23,927 --> 00:48:29,229
- Set cold tab fitting to 200 P.S.I.
- Set.

606
00:48:29,333 --> 00:48:32,700
There she goes. She's breaking loose.
Bringing her up.

607
00:48:32,803 --> 00:48:36,796
<i>Okay. All right.</i>

608
00:48:36,907 --> 00:48:42,743
Get clear of the hatch. Keep goin'
with it. Keep goin'. That's it, up.

609
00:48:42,846 --> 00:48:45,872
Sir, the missile
looks intact.

610
00:48:45,982 --> 00:48:49,247
Little is known at this hour about
the events leading up to the collision.

611
00:48:49,353 --> 00:48:51,821
<i>The U.S. Navy guided missile
cruiser Appleton...</i>

612
00:48:51,922 --> 00:48:55,380
apparently struck
the Soviet destroyer...

613
00:48:55,492 --> 00:48:57,824
in low visibility conditions.

614
00:48:57,928 --> 00:49:01,796
In violent seas, little hope remains
for over 100 Russian crewmen...

615
00:49:01,898 --> 00:49:04,458
still missing after
the sinking an hour ago.

616
00:49:04,568 --> 00:49:07,196
Soviet military spokesmen have
claimed that the collision...

617
00:49:07,304 --> 00:49:09,864
constituted
an unprovoked attack.

618
00:49:09,973 --> 00:49:12,999
<i>- This was denied by state
department officials...
- Bud, this is big time.</i>

619
00:49:13,110 --> 00:49:15,203
<i>Who said that Captain Michael Sweeney
was acting correctly...</i>

620
00:49:15,312 --> 00:49:17,906
Okay, it's clear.

621
00:49:18,014 --> 00:49:20,778
It's all yours, sir.

622
00:49:20,884 --> 00:49:25,583
- Swing it away and drop it.
- Check. Okay.

623
00:49:25,689 --> 00:49:30,149
Bypass the ground connection
on the separation sequencer.

624
00:49:30,260 --> 00:49:35,163
- Got it?
- Separation sequencer disconnected.

625
00:49:35,265 --> 00:49:38,860
Remove explosive bolts one through
six in counterclockwise sequence.

626
00:49:38,969 --> 00:49:40,869
Check.
Removing bolt one.

627
00:49:49,713 --> 00:49:53,444
Negotiators have walked out of
the Strategic Arms Limitation Talks...

628
00:49:53,550 --> 00:49:56,519
- in protest over
the incident this morning...
- [Changes Channel]

629
00:49:56,620 --> 00:50:00,021
[Translator] The sudden deterioration
of relations with the United States...

630
00:50:00,123 --> 00:50:02,853
Soviet buildup of tanks
and aircraft has continued.

631
00:50:02,959 --> 00:50:07,521
Sometime this morning,
all U.S. And NATO military forces
have been put on full alert.

632
00:50:07,631 --> 00:50:09,531
It's on every channel.

633
00:50:09,633 --> 00:50:11,999
Well, you just
feel so helpless.

634
00:50:12,102 --> 00:50:16,562
You can see it coming, but what
can you do? What can anyone do?

635
00:50:16,673 --> 00:50:22,134
Hey, I mean, they love their kids too.
So why are we doin' this?

636
00:50:22,245 --> 00:50:25,112
If it happens,
it happens.

637
00:50:25,215 --> 00:50:29,379
There's nothing I can do about it,
right? I just don't think about it.

638
00:50:44,351 --> 00:50:47,184
All right. Let's get their gear off!
Then clear the sub.

639
00:50:47,287 --> 00:50:50,814
We got to get it out of here!
Come on. Let's go. Let's move it.

640
00:50:50,924 --> 00:50:53,893
One Night, you're up.
Get ready to roll, baby.

641
00:50:53,993 --> 00:50:56,553
<i>- Don't touch that. Just back away.
- Excusez-moi.</i>

642
00:50:59,432 --> 00:51:02,060
Hey, Coffey, we are
a little pressed for time.

643
00:51:06,840 --> 00:51:10,606
Prick. This ain't no drill,
slick. Make me proud.

644
00:51:10,710 --> 00:51:14,077
Piece of cake, baby.

645
00:51:39,906 --> 00:51:41,840
<i>[Loud Banging]</i>

646
00:51:46,346 --> 00:51:48,974
<i>[Bud Over Radio]
What's the problem, One Night?</i>

647
00:51:49,082 --> 00:51:54,247
All hell must be breaking loose
up there. This cable's pissin' me off.

648
00:51:54,354 --> 00:51:58,552
<i>- I can't get a grip on it.
- Well, keep tryin', baby.
Just keep tryin'.</i>

649
00:51:58,658 --> 00:52:01,388
Son of a bitch!

650
00:52:02,729 --> 00:52:05,527
- Shit! We got a problem!
- [Alarm Beeping]

651
00:52:05,632 --> 00:52:08,567
- What's going on?
- We're losing number two thruster!

652
00:52:08,668 --> 00:52:11,398
<i>Bearing's going!</i>

653
00:52:11,504 --> 00:52:15,065
- It's not holding. We're
swinging out of position here!
- Goddamn it!

654
00:52:22,882 --> 00:52:26,409
- [Metal Scraping]
- Ooh! Jesus.

655
00:52:33,626 --> 00:52:35,321
Ah, shit!

656
00:52:46,172 --> 00:52:48,766
- The rig is movin'!
- Yeah, I can see that.

657
00:52:48,875 --> 00:52:51,708
Topside! Pay out some slack.
We're gettin' dragged.

658
00:52:51,811 --> 00:52:54,871
<i>- Down on number one winch!
Down on one!
- We're gettin'dragged!</i>

659
00:53:00,553 --> 00:53:03,545
Bud, we're headed right
for the drop-off.

660
00:53:32,552 --> 00:53:36,579
<i>What the hell?
We just lost all the topside feeds.</i>

661
00:53:39,192 --> 00:53:44,061
Shit! Get him on the U.Q. C.!
Bud!

662
00:53:45,665 --> 00:53:48,031
<i>- We lost the crane!
- Say again. What?</i>

663
00:53:48,134 --> 00:53:52,935
The crane! We've lost the crane!
It's on its way down to you!

664
00:53:53,039 --> 00:53:57,203
All right, everybody.
Everybody, rig for impact!

665
00:53:57,310 --> 00:54:00,211
<i>- [Alarm Blaring]
- Close all the exterior hatches!</i>

666
00:54:00,313 --> 00:54:03,578
<i>[Bud Over P.A.]
Go, go, go, go!</i>

667
00:54:03,683 --> 00:54:05,583
Wait, wait, wait!

668
