01:15:49,336 --> 01:15:51,236
Everybody just stop.

905
01:15:58,078 --> 01:15:59,978
All right,

906
01:16:00,080 --> 01:16:03,481
I want a round-the-clock manning of the
sonar shack and the exterior cameras.

907
01:16:05,185 --> 01:16:08,086
That Russian bogey comes back,
I don't think we should be taking a nap.

908
01:16:08,188 --> 01:16:09,951
Oh, give me a break,
Coffey.

909
01:16:10,057 --> 01:16:12,958
Those things live three-and-a-half
miles down in an abyssal trench.

910
01:16:13,060 --> 01:16:15,460
<i>Trust me, they're not
speaking Russian.</i>

911
01:16:19,800 --> 01:16:23,497
- Have you finished the repairs on
the acoustical transmitter yet?
- Nope.

912
01:16:24,605 --> 01:16:26,664
Why not?

913
01:16:26,774 --> 01:16:28,674
I was having
my nails done.

914
01:16:28,776 --> 01:16:30,676
<i>Well, get it done.</i>

915
01:16:30,778 --> 01:16:32,973
Kiss my ass.

916
01:16:44,692 --> 01:16:46,592
All right,

917
01:16:46,694 --> 01:16:48,594
get somethin' straight.

918
01:16:49,897 --> 01:16:51,797
You people
are under my authority.

919
01:16:51,899 --> 01:16:53,799
<i>- Look, partner...
- When I give you an or...</i>

920
01:16:53,901 --> 01:16:56,734
Look, partner,
we don't work for you,

921
01:16:56,837 --> 01:16:59,135
we don't take orders
from you...

922
01:16:59,239 --> 01:17:01,264
and we don't much like you.

923
01:17:04,178 --> 01:17:06,908
Hey, Cat. Cat!

924
01:17:08,849 --> 01:17:13,377
- Yeah?
- Why don't you take the
first watch on sonar, okay?

925
01:17:14,521 --> 01:17:16,421
Right on.

926
01:17:17,925 --> 01:17:21,827
Sonny, you get a couple hours sleep,
then you spell Cat.

927
01:17:21,929 --> 01:17:24,830
Hippy, you handle
exterior surveillance.

928
01:17:24,932 --> 01:17:26,832
[Shuddering]

929
01:17:26,934 --> 01:17:28,834
One Night.

930
01:17:28,936 --> 01:17:32,531
Would you do me a favor and see if
you can get that transmitter fixed?

931
01:17:32,639 --> 01:17:35,540
- All right?
- Be a couple hours.

932
01:17:44,084 --> 01:17:45,984
- [Click]
- Got it.

933
01:18:08,940 --> 01:18:10,840
All right.

934
01:18:10,942 --> 01:18:15,276
Come on, A.J. Squared-away,
a little to the left.

935
01:18:16,381 --> 01:18:18,281
<i>[Hippy]
What is that?</i>

936
01:18:26,491 --> 01:18:29,051
Oh, this is not happening.

937
01:18:31,629 --> 01:18:33,529
Oh, man.

938
01:18:36,735 --> 01:18:40,432
<i>[Hippy] Look at me. I'm shakin'.
All right, wait, wait, wait.</i>

939
01:18:40,538 --> 01:18:42,438
And now...

940
01:18:42,540 --> 01:18:44,633
here's MI RV.

941
01:18:48,046 --> 01:18:50,606
Come on, man.
What else could it be?

942
01:18:50,715 --> 01:18:52,615
Why bring it here?

943
01:18:52,717 --> 01:18:56,744
It's gotta be some kind of emergency
plan to keep it away from the Russians.

944
01:18:56,855 --> 01:18:59,756
Look, they hot-wire
one of the nukes,

945
01:18:59,858 --> 01:19:02,759
they use some kind of detonator
that they brought,

946
01:19:02,861 --> 01:19:06,262
then they stick it back in the sub,
fry the whole thing up.

947
01:19:06,364 --> 01:19:08,764
Bam! Slicker than snot.

948
01:19:10,668 --> 01:19:13,694
I'm tellin' ya.
And I'm not bein' paranoi...

949
01:19:14,906 --> 01:19:16,806
Hi, Linds.

950
01:19:24,415 --> 01:19:26,815
Linds, will you just
wait a second.

951
01:19:26,918 --> 01:19:29,819
Goddamn it, if you don't
do something about it, I will!

952
01:19:29,921 --> 01:19:33,152
Lindsey, we'll do something about it!
Just wait a second!

953
01:19:33,258 --> 01:19:35,158
- Lindsey.
- What?

954
01:19:35,260 --> 01:19:37,251
- Just stop and think about this.
- What?

955
01:19:37,362 --> 01:19:39,421
<i>[Banging Continues]</i>

956
01:19:58,082 --> 01:20:01,074
<i>You got some huevos
bringing that thing into my rig.</i>

957
01:20:02,921 --> 01:20:06,652
With all that's going on
up in the world, you bring
a nuclear weapon in here?

958
01:20:06,758 --> 01:20:08,658
Mrs. Brigman...

959
01:20:08,760 --> 01:20:12,662
Does this strike anyone as particularly
psychotic, or is it just me?

960
01:20:12,764 --> 01:20:16,165
Mrs. Brigman, you don't need to know
the details of our operation.

961
01:20:16,267 --> 01:20:18,167
It's better if you don't.

962
01:20:18,269 --> 01:20:20,169
You're right.
I don't need to know.

963
01:20:20,271 --> 01:20:24,230
What I need to know
is that thing is off this rig!
Do you hear me, Roger Ramjet?

964
01:20:25,944 --> 01:20:29,004
You're becoming
a serious impediment to our mission.

965
01:20:29,113 --> 01:20:32,207
Now, you either do an about-face
and walk out of here,

966
01:20:32,317 --> 01:20:34,217
or I'll have you
escorted out.

967
01:20:34,319 --> 01:20:37,482
I will not do an about-face
and get out of here.

968
01:20:37,589 --> 01:20:39,989
- Who do you think you're talking...
- [Alarm Bell Rings]

969
01:20:40,091 --> 01:20:42,889
Emergency! Maintenance Room B!
Everybody move it!

970
01:20:42,994 --> 01:20:45,326
<i>- On the double!
- Now! Now!</i>

971
01:20:45,430 --> 01:20:48,558
<i>- [Alarm Continues]
- In here! Come on! We've got trouble!</i>

972
01:20:48,666 --> 01:20:50,566
- Now! Come on!
- What's goin' on?

973
01:20:50,668 --> 01:20:54,035
<i>- All right, all right,
all right, all right!
- [Alarm Stops]</i>

974
01:20:54,138 --> 01:20:56,038
<i>[One Night]
What's up? What's happening?</i>

975
01:20:56,140 --> 01:20:58,870
You let her go, man.
Do it. Do it now!

976
01:20:59,978 --> 01:21:01,411
Let her go.

977
01:21:01,512 --> 01:21:03,412
[Grunts]

978
01:21:03,514 --> 01:21:06,074
That was the smartest thing
you ever did.

979
01:21:09,654 --> 01:21:12,214
- Coffey, you son of a bitch...
- Lindsey! Cool it.

980
01:21:12,323 --> 01:21:14,883
<i>- [Cat] What's the problem?
- Nothin'.</i>

981
01:21:14,993 --> 01:21:17,086
We were just leaving.
Weren't we?

982
01:21:37,515 --> 01:21:39,915
W-We don't need them.

983
01:21:41,052 --> 01:21:42,952
We can't trust them.

984
01:21:47,025 --> 01:21:49,926
We may have to take steps.

985
01:21:51,829 --> 01:21:54,229
We're gonna have to
take steps.

986
01:21:58,536 --> 01:22:01,437
Linds, I want you to stay away
from that guy.

987
01:22:01,539 --> 01:22:03,803
- I mean it.
- The guy is gone.

988
01:22:03,908 --> 01:22:05,808
Did you see his hands?

989
01:22:05,910 --> 01:22:07,810
What? He's got the shakes?

990
01:22:07,912 --> 01:22:09,812
Look, he's operating
on his own,

991
01:22:09,914 --> 01:22:12,314
he's cut off from
his chain of command,

992
01:22:12,417 --> 01:22:15,648
he's showing signs
of pressure-induced psychosis...

993
01:22:15,753 --> 01:22:18,654
and he's got
a nuclear weapon.

994
01:22:18,756 --> 01:22:22,658
So, as a favor to me, try to put
your tongue in neutral for a while.

995
01:22:22,760 --> 01:22:27,663
I gotta tell you, I give this whole
thing a sphincter factor of about 9.5.

996
01:23:06,203 --> 01:23:10,105
Look, you can just punch into
his primary guidance chip
where you want him to go...

997
01:23:10,207 --> 01:23:12,107
and he'll go there,
right?

998
01:23:12,209 --> 01:23:14,609
- No. Bad idea, Lindsey. Bad.
- Why? Hip, come on.

999
01:23:14,712 --> 01:23:17,613
Because even if it could
take the pressure at that depth,

1000
01:23:17,715 --> 01:23:19,615
- which I don't think it can,
- Yeah?

1001
01:23:19,717 --> 01:23:22,618
Without the tether you know what'd
happen when it got down there?

1002
01:23:22,720 --> 01:23:24,620
It would just sit like...
Please.

1003
01:23:24,722 --> 01:23:27,122
It would just sit
like a dumb shit.

1004
01:23:27,224 --> 01:23:30,625
Something would have to pass in front
of the camera for you to see anything.

1005
01:23:30,728 --> 01:23:33,788
But we could get lucky, right?
So we should go for it.

1006
01:23:33,898 --> 01:23:37,299
- I really ought to talk
to Bud about this.
- This is between you and me.

1007
01:23:37,401 --> 01:23:40,131
We get proof,
and then we tell the others.

1008
01:23:40,237 --> 01:23:44,469
If we can prove to Coffey
that there aren't Russians down there,

1009
01:23:44,575 --> 01:23:47,976
maybe he'll ease off the button
a little bit.

1010
01:23:48,078 --> 01:23:52,947
I gotta tell ya, that guy
scares me more than anything
we're gonna find down there.

1011
01:23:53,050 --> 01:23:57,350
He's a goddamn A.J. Squared-away,
jar-head robot.

1012
01:23:57,454 --> 01:23:58,978
It's...

1013
01:24:00,424 --> 01:24:03,325
All right, give me a couple hours
to see what I can do.

1014
01:24:03,427 --> 01:24:04,951
Great. Thanks.

1015
01:24:13,470 --> 01:24:15,370
How's that?

1016
01:24:19,176 --> 01:24:21,076
Thanks.

1017
01:24:35,759 --> 01:24:38,660
[Snoring]

1018
01:24:43,033 --> 01:24:45,433
Virgil, turn on your side.

1019
01:24:52,243 --> 01:24:54,108
[Pinging]

1020
01:24:55,646 --> 01:24:57,477
[Static,
Pinging Continues]

1021
01:25:14,798 --> 01:25:17,699
All right,
you're all set, big guy.

1022
01:25:17,801 --> 01:25:21,202
Hey, I told you
to wipe that grin off your face.

1023
01:25:29,913 --> 01:25:31,813
Good night,
little buddy.

1024
01:27:18,125 --> 01:27:20,650
[Gasps]

1025
01:27:20,761 --> 01:27:23,252
[Whispers]
Bud. Bud. Bud!

1026
01:27:23,364 --> 01:27:25,264
Get up.

1027
01:27:27,234 --> 01:27:29,134
What?

1028
01:27:38,979 --> 01:27:40,879
Cat.

1029
01:27:42,449 --> 01:27:44,417
- Cat!
- Hey!

1030
01:27:44,518 --> 01:27:46,918
[Mumbling]
God... Leave me alone.

1031
01:27:47,021 --> 01:27:48,921
[Gasps]

1032
01:27:54,828 --> 01:27:56,819
Bud.

1033
01:27:59,266 --> 01:28:01,734
Wait. It's okay.

1034
01:28:01,835 --> 01:28:03,735
Sweet Christ Almighty.

1035
01:28:03,837 --> 01:28:06,635
I think it likes you.

1036
01:28:25,092 --> 01:28:27,356
It's trying to communicate.

1037
01:28:29,129 --> 01:28:31,188
<i>[One Night]
That's Bud.</i>

1038
01:28:31,298 --> 01:28:33,357
[Laughing]

1039
01:28:33,467 --> 01:28:35,367
It's wonderful.

1040
01:28:35,469 --> 01:28:37,369
It's me.

1041
01:28:40,674 --> 01:28:42,665
- No, no, no.
- Shh. It's okay.

1042
01:28:42,776 --> 01:28:44,505
<i>[One Night]
What is it?</i>

1043
01:28:47,381 --> 01:28:49,747
<i>[One Night]
Is it alive?</i>

1044
01:28:52,453 --> 01:28:54,512
<i>[Bud]
Lindsey, no.</i>

1045
01:28:56,156 --> 01:28:58,522
Sea water.

1046
01:28:58,625 --> 01:29:00,456
<i>[One Night]
Oh, man.</i>

1047
01:29:13,273 --> 01:29:15,537
Come on. Come on!

1048
01:29:17,444 --> 01:29:20,038
- Hurry!
- Where the hell's it goin'?

1049
01:29:21,548 --> 01:29:23,448
Huh?

1050
01:29:30,524 --> 01:29:33,425
<i>Hurry! I think it's headed
for "B"module.</i>

1051
01:29:33,527 --> 01:29:35,427
Linds, you see it?

1052
01:29:49,543 --> 01:29:51,443
[Gasps]

1053
01:29:58,418 --> 01:30:01,353
[Shuddering, Grunting]

1054
01:30:05,092 --> 01:30:06,992
- Aah!
- Aah!

1055
01:30:10,397 --> 01:30:12,456
Aaah!

1056
01:30:16,470 --> 01:30:18,870
[Shivering]

1057
01:30:23,076 --> 01:30:25,476
[Whimpering,
Continues Shivering]

1058
01:30:26,747 --> 01:30:29,648
[Static Stops]

1059
01:30:31,018 --> 01:30:32,986
[Pinging Continues]

1060
01:30:35,722 --> 01:30:39,351
<i>[Lindsey] So, raise your hand if you
think that was a Russian water tentacle.</i>

1061
01:30:40,460 --> 01:30:42,360
Lieutenant?

1062
01:30:42,462 --> 01:30:44,362
No? Well.

1063
01:30:45,465 --> 01:30:47,365
A breakthrough.

1064
01:30:47,467 --> 01:30:50,595
Hey, Ace, you done
impressin' yourself?

1065
01:30:50,704 --> 01:30:53,935
No way that thing
could just be sea water.

1066
01:30:54,041 --> 01:30:58,671
They must have learned to control water.
I mean at a molecular level.

1067
01:30:58,779 --> 01:31:02,180
They can plasticize it, polymerize it,
do whatever they want to do with it.

1068
01:31:02,282 --> 01:31:05,183
They can put it
under intelligent control.

1069
01:31:05,285 --> 01:31:09,051
Maybe their whole technology's
based on that.

1070
01:31:09,156 --> 01:31:10,987
<i>- What?
- Controlling water.</i>

1071
01:31:12,659 --> 01:31:16,857
<i>- [Hippy] Was it the same thing
that you saw the last time?
- No.</i>

1072
01:31:16,964 --> 01:31:20,559
You know, I don't think that
that thing you saw was one of them.

1073
01:31:20,667 --> 01:31:24,068
- What are you talking about?
- I mean, I don't think it was an N.T.I.

1074
01:31:24,171 --> 01:31:27,902
I think it was their version
of an R.O.V., like Big Geek.

1075
01:31:29,543 --> 01:31:32,944
<i>- [Cat] Hippy, you mean
they was just checkin'us out?
- Yeah.</i>

1076
01:31:33,046 --> 01:31:35,446
<i>- How come?
- [Lindsey] Curious, I suppose.</i>

1077
01:31:35,549 --> 01:31:39,451
<i>We're probably the first people
that have ever seen one.
Who's been down this far?</i>

1078
01:31:39,553 --> 01:31:43,455
<i>- [Grunting]
- [Cat] Sure hope they don't
judge the rest of us by him.</i>

1079
01:31:51,365 --> 01:31:53,265
[Grunts]

1080
01:31:55,602 --> 01:31:57,433
Went straight
for the warhead,

1081
01:31:57,537 --> 01:31:59,437
and they think it's cute.

1082
01:32:18,525 --> 01:32:20,425
You need to get
some sleep.

1083
01:32:30,737 --> 01:32:33,297
[Panting]
We have no way...

1084
01:32:33,407 --> 01:32:36,467
of warning the surface.

1085
01:32:36,576 --> 01:32:38,976
You know what that means?

1086
01:32:41,548 --> 01:32:44,312
It means whatever happens...

1087
01:32:44,418 --> 01:32:46,318
is up to us.

1088
01:32:47,688 --> 01:32:49,087
Us.

1089
01:33:29,463 --> 01:33:32,364
[Grunting]

1090
01:33:57,290 --> 01:34:00,691
<i>[One Night] So you think
they're from down there originally,</i>

1091
01:34:00,794 --> 01:34:04,093
<i>or from, you know...</i>

1092
01:34:04,197 --> 01:34:06,893
[Laughs]
I don't know.

1093
01:34:07,000 --> 01:34:09,560
I think...
I think they're from "you know."

1094
01:34:09,669 --> 01:34:12,900
<i>Someplace with similar conditions...
cold, intense pressure.</i>

1095
01:34:13,006 --> 01:34:14,906
Oh, man.

1096
01:34:15,008 --> 01:34:18,273
Happy as hogs in a waller
down there, probably.

1097
01:34:18,378 --> 01:34:20,903
<i>[Metallic Spinning Sound]</i>

1098
01:34:21,014 --> 01:34:22,914
[Gasps]

1099
01:34:27,521 --> 01:34:31,423
<i>[Spinning Sound Continues]</i>

1100
01:34:45,221 --> 01:34:48,247
<i>[Spinning Sound Continues, Louder]</i>

1101
01:35:12,147 --> 01:35:14,047
[Gasps]

1102
01:35:16,652 --> 01:35:18,552
Sniff somethin'?

1103
01:35:22,157 --> 01:35:24,057
Did you, rat boy?

1104
01:35:25,661 --> 01:35:27,288
[Grunts]

1105
01:35:28,397 --> 01:35:30,922
- [Grunting]
- Hey, hey, hey!

1106
01:35:31,033 --> 01:35:33,593
Freeze! Don't move!

1107
01:35:34,937 --> 01:35:36,666
That's right.

1108
01:35:38,107 --> 01:35:40,098
You okay, Hip?

1109
01:35:40,209 --> 01:35:43,610
- They're using Big Geek
to take the bomb to the N.T.I.s.
- What?

1110
01:35:43,712 --> 01:35:46,840
- We set it up to go right to 'em.
- Oh, my God.

1111
01:35:46,949 --> 01:35:48,849
Oh, my God.

1112
01:35:48,951 --> 01:35:51,010
Take this.
We're going to phase three.

1113
01:35:51,120 --> 01:35:54,521
[Groaning]
What? We don't have orders for that!

1114
01:35:54,623 --> 01:35:56,454
<i>[Hippy]
I programmed Big Geek...</i>

1115
01:35:56,558 --> 01:35:59,459
<i>to go down to the bottom of the trench
and shoot some video.</i>

1116
01:35:59,561 --> 01:36:03,122
<i>- Now they've got the warhead tied to it.
- Coffey?</i>

1117
01:36:05,234 --> 01:36:07,464
- Linds...
- Coffey... No. Come on.

1118
01:36:07,569 --> 01:36:10,470
Just think about
what you're doing just one minute.

1119
01:36:10,572 --> 01:36:12,665
Just think about
what you're... Aaah!

1120
01:36:12,775 --> 01:36:15,107
Get back!

1121
01:36:15,210 --> 01:36:19,544
This is something
I've wanted to do since we first met.

1122
01:36:19,648 --> 01:36:22,344
<i>[Tearing]</i>

1123
01:36:23,819 --> 01:36:26,379
[Whimpers]

1124
01:36:27,523 --> 01:36:30,048
Easy. Easy.
Take it easy.

1125
01:36:30,159 --> 01:36:32,059
- [Grunting]
- [Lindsey Moaning]

1126
01:36:32,161 --> 01:36:34,061
Into the kitchen.
Let's go.

1127
01:36:34,163 --> 01:36:36,063
- Move, partner!
- Get your damn hands off of me!

1128
01:36:36,165 --> 01:36:38,065
- Get in there!
- I know the way.

1129
01:36:38,167 --> 01:36:41,568
Your boss is fixin'
to pull the pin on 50 kilotons,

1130
01:36:41,670 --> 01:36:44,400
and we're all
gonna be ringside!

1131
01:36:44,506 --> 01:36:46,906
<i>He's having
a full-on meltdown!</i>

1132
01:36:47,009 --> 01:36:49,375
<i>- What's the timer set for?
- Three hours.</i>

1133
01:36:49,478 --> 01:36:51,378
<i>- Shut up. Don't talk.
- Three hours?</i>

1134
01:36:51,480 --> 01:36:55,814
We can't get to minimum safe distance
in three hours.

1135
01:36:55,918 --> 01:36:59,251
- We can't go to phase three.
What about these people?
- Shut up.

