1711
02:36:36,243 --> 02:36:38,871
<i>You boys make up your mind
how to get us out of here yet?</i>

1712
02:36:38,979 --> 02:36:41,413
They're talking about flying
in a D.S.R.V. From Norfolk.

1713
02:36:41,515 --> 02:36:45,713
- Just wish I could've seen it.
- Okay, how long is that gonna take?

1714
02:36:45,819 --> 02:36:49,949
How do you stop
a half-mile high tidal wave in...

1715
02:36:53,827 --> 02:36:57,194
Hey. Hey. Hey, it's Bud!

1716
02:36:57,297 --> 02:37:00,357
That's impossible.

1717
02:37:00,467 --> 02:37:03,868
<i>- [Bud Over Radio] Do you read me,
Deep Core? Do you hear?
- No, it's not.</i>

1718
02:37:03,971 --> 02:37:08,465
- Yes!
- W-Wait. We got a message from Bud.

1719
02:37:08,575 --> 02:37:11,373
- Bud?
- What's it say?

1720
02:37:11,478 --> 02:37:14,276
Here. Here.

1721
02:37:14,381 --> 02:37:17,748
Oh. It says...

1722
02:37:17,851 --> 02:37:21,446
It says, "Virgil Brigman
back on the air."

1723
02:37:21,555 --> 02:37:24,046
<i>- [All Laughing]
- Yes!</i>

1724
02:37:34,434 --> 02:37:37,096
"Have some new friends
down here.

1725
02:37:37,204 --> 02:37:39,604
Guess they've been here a while."

1726
02:37:49,516 --> 02:37:53,452
"They've left us alone, but it bothers
them to see us hurting each other."

1727
02:37:56,924 --> 02:38:00,087
"Getting out of hand."

1728
02:38:07,768 --> 02:38:10,430
"They sent a message.
Hope you got it."

1729
02:38:10,537 --> 02:38:14,906
I'd say that's a big 10-4,Jack.

1730
02:38:15,008 --> 02:38:19,104
<i>"They want us to grow up a bit
and put away childish things. "</i>

1731
02:38:20,914 --> 02:38:24,645
"Of course,
it's just a suggestion."

1732
02:38:27,654 --> 02:38:31,112
<i>[Laughter Continues]</i>

1733
02:38:32,926 --> 02:38:35,622
Looks like you boys
might be out of business.

1734
